# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Express + S3 file upload/download app with CloudMock for local development.

## Getting Started

### 1. Start CloudMock

```bash
docker compose up
# or
npx cloudmock
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 3. Run the app

```bash
npm start
```

## API

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | /upload?key=filename | Upload a file |
| GET | /files | List all files |
| GET | /files/:key | Download a file |

Example:

```bash
# Upload
curl -X POST "http://localhost:3000/upload?key=notes.txt" \
  -H "Content-Type: text/plain" \
  --data-binary "Hello from CloudMock"

# Download
curl http://localhost:3000/files/notes.txt

# List
curl http://localhost:3000/files
```

## Testing

```bash
npm test
```

Tests use `@cloudmock/sdk` — no Docker required.

